VAn erudite concert
p3
sVnews
p4
VSangeetha Kalaasamithi recently featured a recital by the reputed vocalist Gaanakalaa Bharathi Manda Sudha Rani.The concert was held at its usual venue for their monthly concerts and festivals - the serene premises of Sadgurubrahma Ramadoota Mandiram.She was given excellent company by her esteemed guru Ivaturi Vijayeswara Rao on violin, veteran artiste V.V. Ramana Murthy on mridangam, along with young Mandapaka Ravi on Kanjeera.A name synonymous with the quintessence of the most cherished form of the sedate and reposeful melodious style of exposition, Sudha, exploiting the timbre of expression in her voice to the hilt, showcased  the inveterate solemnity sublimely invested in Carnatic music by the vaggeyakaras of the yore.Song listAfter a  resonant start with theBilhari varnamsuffixed with scintillatingswaram, she absorbingly rendered theSourashtra Devaranaama,Saranu Siddhivinayaka(Chaapu Talam).She then went on to singNiravadhisukhada(Ravichandrika),Deva Deva(Purvikalyani),Bhogeendra Sayinam(Kuntalavarali) andGovardhana Girisam(Hindolam), before she took upEmineramo Nannubrova(Sankarabharanam) for expansive expatiation.All except theKuntalavarali krithihad effulgent embellishments ofalapanaandswaramin two speeds, which turned out to be an effort fortifying the devout emotions embedded both in the lyrical and musical components of the compositions.The  elaboration of the item inSankarabharanamin all aspects ofalapana,neravuandswaramin the two speeds turned out to be a sumptuous feast of discernible knowledge, technique and scholarship.Vijayeswra Rao was equally erudite on violin, especially during his turns,  Ramana Murthy along with Ravi going not only tidily invigorative in his following but also aesthetically virtuosic in executing vibrantthanicontributed grandeur.Ravi as well proved his proficiency in his turns inthani.A. R. S.Bottom Template Starts
